<rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>救生艇新闻：博客——保护人类</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/</link><description></description><lastBuildDate>Fri, 22 May 2026 14:13:14 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>rfeed v1.1.1</generator><docs>https://github.com/svpino/rfeed/blob/master/README.md</docs><item><title>海马 CA3 记忆回路中稀疏和结构化突触连接的发展出现</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/developmental-emergence-of-sparse-and-structured-synaptic-connectivity-in-the-hippocampal-ca3-memory-circuit</link><description>作者利用多细胞膜片钳记录表明，海马 CA3 自联想网络在出生后发育过程中经历了 CA3-CA3 突触的修剪和突触功效的下调，这表明编码特性和记忆功能发生了双重转变。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/developmental-emergence-of-sparse-and-structured-synaptic-connectivity-in-the-hippocampal-ca3-memory-circuit.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Fri, 22 May 2026 14:13:12 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/developmental-emergence-of-sparse-and-structured-synaptic-connectivity-in-the-hippocampal-ca3-memory-circuit</guid></item><item><title>研究显示，在线“幕后”出现新型黑暗旅游</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/new-kind-of-dark-tourism-emerging-in-online-backrooms-study-shows</link><description>兰卡斯特大学的最新发现表明，数字文化正在重塑人们的恐惧、好奇和归属感体验。研究人员探索了为什么像“密室”这样的在线环境——类似于未知办公楼、地下室和走廊的神秘空旷空间——变得如此引人注目，以及为什么人们选择迷失在不存在的空间中。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/new-kind-of-dark-tourism-emerging-in-online-backrooms-study-shows.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Fri, 22 May 2026 13:58:12 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/new-kind-of-dark-tourism-emerging-in-online-backrooms-study-shows</guid></item><item><title>多重 MRI 提供人脑的全面视图</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/multiplexed-mri-provides-a-comprehensive-view-of-the-human-brain</link><description>使用标准临床 MRI 系统的新型多重成像技术可以同时以高分辨率绘制 20 多种生物标记物，通过单次扫描提供大脑的全面视图。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/multiplexed-mri-provides-a-comprehensive-view-of-the-human-brain2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Fri, 22 May 2026 13:43:12 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/multiplexed-mri-provides-a-comprehensive-view-of-the-human-brain</guid></item><item><title>胶质瘤 CAR-T 疗法的反复局限性：来自临床前和 I 期临床研究的证据</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/recurrent-limitations-of-car-t-therapy-in-gliomas-evidence-from-preclinical-and-phase-i-clinical-studies</link><description>近年来，新的免疫治疗策略的发展是癌症治疗的重大突破。其中，嵌合抗原受体工程化T细胞疗法（CAR-T）已产生显着的临床效果，特别是在血液恶性肿瘤方面。这一成功引发了人们对将 CAR-T 应用于实体瘤（包括神经胶质瘤）的兴趣日益增长。胶质瘤，特别是多形性胶质母细胞瘤 (GBM)，是最具侵袭性的原发性脑肿瘤之一，预后不良，诊断后中位生存期约为一年。然而，将 CAR-T 疗法转化为神经胶质瘤面临着重大挑战，这与肿瘤异质性、血脑屏障 (BBB) 的存在以及强烈的免疫抑制肿瘤环境等因素有关。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/recurrent-limitations-of-car-t-therapy-in-gliomas-evidence-from-preclinical-and-phase-i-clinical-studies.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Fri, 22 May 2026 13:28:12 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/recurrent-limitations-of-car-t-therapy-in-gliomas-evidence-from-preclinical-and-phase-i-clinical-studies</guid></item><item><title>阿尔茨海默病的神经递质系统</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/neurotransmitter-systems-in-alzheimers-disease</link><description>阿尔茨海默病 (AD) 是全球痴呆症的主要原因，它是一个多因素过程，不仅限于 β-淀粉样蛋白 (Aβ) 斑块和 tau 蛋白缠结的积累，还包括神经胶质细胞介导的神经炎症、血管功能障碍、代谢改变和突触损失。其复杂的病因还涉及氧化应激和线粒体功能障碍。参与 AD 发病机制的多种神经递质系统以及 AD 的各种认知和非认知症状因此而改变。历史上第一个与 AD 相关的胆碱能系统遭受早期退化和神经元/受体丧失，与认知障碍相关。谷氨酸能系统是主要的兴奋系统，由于细胞外谷氨酸增加和 NMDA/AMPA 受体分布改变而表现出兴奋性毒性，加剧神经元损伤。&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/neurotransmitter-systems-in-alzheimers-disease.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Fri, 22 May 2026 13:13:12 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/neurotransmitter-systems-in-alzheimers-disease</guid></item><item><title>英国最危险的皮肤癌病例创历史新高</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/riskiest-skin-cancer-cases-hit-uk-record-high</link><description>英国每年黑色素瘤皮肤癌病例数首次超过 20,000 例。&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/riskiest-skin-cancer-cases-hit-uk-record-high.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Fri, 22 May 2026 12:58:12 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/riskiest-skin-cancer-cases-hit-uk-record-high</guid></item><item><title>构建口服肽药物</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/building-an-oral-peptide-drug</link><description>工程酶能够在高胆固醇条件下实现公斤级药物合成&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/building-an-oral-peptide-drug2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Fri, 22 May 2026 12:43:12 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/building-an-oral-peptide-drug</guid></item><item><title>将自旋扭转成自旋波透镜</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/twisting-spins-into-a-spin-wave-lens</link><description>材料的扭曲磁性结构可用于在未来的自旋电子器件中聚焦或准直自旋波。&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/twisting-spins-into-a-spin-wave-lens2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Fri, 22 May 2026 12:28:12 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/twisting-spins-into-a-spin-wave-lens</guid></item><item><title>手性碲出现不寻常的非线性热电效应，证实了理论预测</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/unusual-nonlinear-thermoelectric-effect-appears-in-chiral-tellurium-confirming-theoretical-predictions</link><description>日本理化学研究所的物理学家首次在半导体碲中观察到了不寻常的热电效应。该演示表明了类似材料在能量收集和先进热管理等应用中的潜力。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/unusual-nonlinear-thermoelectric-effect-appears-in-chiral-tellurium-confirming-theoretical-predictions.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Fri, 22 May 2026 12:13:12 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/unusual-nonlinear-thermoelectric-effect-appears-in-chiral-tellurium-confirming-theoretical-predictions</guid></item><item><title>理论物理学家认为，当电荷和霍金辐射结合时，黑洞可能会避免奇点</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/black-holes-may-avoid-singularities-when-charge-and-hawking-radiation-combine-theoretical-physicist-argues</link><description>黑洞是太空中的区域，其引力非常强大，任何东西（甚至光）都无法逃脱。爱因斯坦的广义相对论在黑洞内部因所谓的“曲率奇点”或“柯西视界”的存在而崩溃。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/black-holes-may-avoid-singularities-when-charge-and-hawking-radiation-combine-theoretical-physicist-argues.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Fri, 22 May 2026 11:58:12 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/black-holes-may-avoid-singularities-when-charge-and-hawking-radiation-combine-theoretical-physicist-argues</guid></item></channel></rss>